SIMPLE: photoglyphic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photoglyphic
<hw>Pho`to*glyph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>gly`fein</grk> to engrave.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to the art of engraving by the action of light.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>photoglyptic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Photoglyphic engraving</b></col>, <cd>a process of
etching on copper, steel, or zinc, by means of the action of light and
certain chemicals, so that from the plate impressions may be taken.</cd>
<rj><au>Sir D. Brewster.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photoglyphy</ent>⟦br⟧
